#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1801
msgid ""
"`#5565 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/5565>`_: Removed unused "
"support code for `unittest2 <https://pypi.org/project/unittest2/>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1803
msgid ""
"The ``unittest2`` backport module is no longer necessary since Python 3.3+, "
"and the small amount of code in pytest to support it also doesn't seem to be "
"used: after removed, all tests still pass unchanged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1807
msgid ""
"Although our policy is to introduce a deprecation period before removing any "
"features or support for third party libraries, because this code is "
"apparently not used at all (even if ``unittest2`` is used by a test suite "
"executed by pytest), it was decided to remove it in this release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1812
msgid ""
"If you experience a regression because of this, please `file an issue "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/new>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1816
msgid ""
"`#5615 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/5615>`_: ``pytest."
"fail``, ``pytest.xfail`` and ``pytest.skip`` no longer support bytes for the "
"message argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1818
msgid ""
"This was supported for Python 2 where it was tempting to use ``\"message\"`` "
"instead of ``u\"message\"``."
