"See https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/deprecations.html#raises-warns-exec "
"for rationale and examples."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3108
msgid ""
"`#3191 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3191>`_: A warning is "
"now issued when assertions are made for ``None``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3110
msgid "This is a common source of confusion among new users, which write:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3112
msgid "assert mocked_object.assert_called_with(3, 4, 5, key=\"value\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3116
msgid "When they should write:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3118
msgid "mocked_object.assert_called_with(3, 4, 5, key=\"value\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3122
msgid ""
"Because the ``assert_called_with`` method of mock objects already executes "
"an assertion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3124
msgid ""
"This warning will not be issued when ``None`` is explicitly checked. An "
"assertion like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3126
msgid "assert variable is None"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3130
msgid "will not issue the warning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3133
msgid ""
"`#3632 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3632>`_: Richer equality "
"comparison introspection on ``AssertionError`` for objects created using "
"`attrs <http://www.attrs.org/en/stable/>`__ or `dataclasses <https://docs."
"python.org/3/library/dataclasses.html>`_ (Python 3.7+, `backported to 3.6 "
"<https://pypi.org/project/dataclasses>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3136
msgid ""
"`#4278 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4278>`_: ``CACHEDIR."
"TAG`` files are now created inside cache directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3138
msgid ""
"Those files are part of the `Cache Directory Tagging Standard <http://www."
"bford.info/cachedir/spec.html>`__, and can be used by backup or "
"synchronization programs to identify pytest's cache directory as such."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3142
msgid ""
"`#4292 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4292>`_: ``pytest."
"outcomes.Exit`` is derived from ``SystemExit`` instead of "
"``KeyboardInterrupt``. This allows us to better handle ``pdb`` exiting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3145
msgid ""
"`#4371 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4371>`_: Updated the ``--"
