msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3148
msgid ""
"`#4386 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4386>`_: Restructured "
"``ExceptionInfo`` object construction and ensure incomplete instances have a "
"``repr``/``str``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3151
msgid ""
"`#4416 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4416>`_: pdb: added "
"support for keyword arguments with ``pdb.set_trace``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3153
msgid ""
"It handles ``header`` similar to Python 3.7 does it, and forwards any other "
"keyword arguments to the ``Pdb`` constructor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3156
msgid "This allows for ``__import__(\"pdb\").set_trace(skip=[\"foo.*\"])``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3159
msgid ""
"`#4483 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4483>`_: Added ini "
"parameter ``junit_duration_report`` to optionally report test call "
"durations, excluding setup and teardown times."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3161
msgid ""
"The JUnit XML specification and the default pytest behavior is to include "
"setup and teardown times in the test duration report. You can include just "
"the call durations instead (excluding setup and teardown) by adding this to "
"your ``pytest.ini`` file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3164
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"junit_duration_report = call"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3170
msgid ""
"`#4532 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4532>`_: ``-ra`` now "
"will show errors and failures last, instead of as the first items in the "
