msgid ""
"**The affected features will be effectively removed in pytest 4.1**, so "
"please consult the `Deprecations and Removals <https://docs.pytest.org/en/"
"stable/deprecations.html>`__ section in the docs for directions on how to "
"update existing code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3298
msgid ""
"In the pytest ``4.0.X`` series, it is possible to change the errors back "
"into warnings as a stop gap measure by adding this to your ``pytest.ini`` "
"file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3301
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"filterwarnings =\n"
"    ignore::pytest.RemovedInPytest4Warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3307
msgid "But this will stop working when pytest ``4.1`` is released."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3309
msgid ""
"**If you have concerns** about the removal of a specific feature, please add "
"a comment to `#4348 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4348>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3313
msgid ""
"`#4358 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4358>`_: Remove the ``::"
"()`` notation to denote a test class instance in node ids."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3315
msgid ""
"Previously, node ids that contain test instances would use ``::()`` to "
"denote the instance like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3317
msgid "test_foo.py::Test::()::test_bar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3319
msgid ""
"The extra ``::()`` was puzzling to most users and has been removed, so that "
"the test id becomes now::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3321
msgid "test_foo.py::Test::test_bar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3323
msgid ""
"This change could not accompany a deprecation period as is usual when user-"
"facing functionality changes because it was not really possible to detect "
"when the functionality was being used explicitly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3326
msgid ""
"The extra ``::()`` might have been removed in some places internally "
"already, which then led to confusion in places where it was expected, e.g. "
"with ``--deselect`` (`#4127 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/4127>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3330
