#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8373
msgid "1.3.1 (2010-05-25)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8377
msgid ""
"issue91: introduce new py.test.xfail(reason) helper to imperatively mark a "
"test as expected to fail. Can be used from within setup and test functions. "
"This is useful especially for parametrized tests when certain configurations "
"are expected-to-fail.  In this case the declarative approach with the @py."
"test.mark.xfail cannot be used as it would mark all configurations as xfail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8385
msgid ""
"issue102: introduce new --maxfail=NUM option to stop test runs after NUM "
"failures.  This is a generalization of the '-x' or '--exitfirst' option "
"which is now equivalent to '--maxfail=1'.  Both '-x' and '--maxfail' will "
"now also print a line near the end indicating the Interruption."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8391
msgid ""
"issue89: allow py.test.mark decorators to be used on classes (class "
"decorators were introduced with python2.6) and also allow to have multiple "
"markers applied at class/module level by specifying a list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8396
msgid ""
"improve and refine letter reporting in the progress bar: .  pass f  failed "
"test s  skipped tests (reminder: use for dependency/platform mismatch only) "
"x  xfailed test (test that was expected to fail) X  xpassed test (test that "
"was expected to fail but passed)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8403
msgid ""
"You can use any combination of 'fsxX' with the '-r' extended reporting "
"option. The xfail/xpass results will show up as skipped tests in the "
"junitxml output - which also fixes issue99."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8408
msgid ""
"make py.test.cmdline.main() return the exitstatus instead of raising "
"SystemExit and also allow it to be called multiple times.  This of course "
"requires that your application and tests are properly teared down and don't "
"have global state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8415
msgid ""
"improved traceback presentation: - improved and unified reporting for \"--"
"tb=short\" option - Errors during test module imports are much shorter, "
"(using --tb=short style) - raises shows shorter more relevant tracebacks - --"
"fulltrace now more systematically makes traces longer / inhibits cutting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8421
msgid ""
"improve support for raises and other dynamically compiled code by "
"manipulating python's linecache.cache instead of the previous rather hacky "
"way of creating custom code objects.  This makes it seemlessly work on "
"Jython and PyPy where it previously didn't."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8426
msgid ""
"fix issue96: make capturing more resilient against Control-C interruptions "
"(involved somewhat substantial refactoring to the underlying capturing "
"functionality to avoid race conditions)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8431
msgid ""
"fix chaining of conditional skipif/xfail decorators - so it works now as "
"expected to use multiple @py.test.mark.skipif(condition) decorators, "
"including specific reporting which of the conditions lead to skipping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8435
msgid ""
"fix issue95: late-import zlib so that it's not required for general py.test "
"startup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8438
msgid ""
"fix issue94: make reporting more robust against bogus source code (and "
"internally be more careful when presenting unexpected byte sequences)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8443
msgid "1.3.0 (2010-05-05)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8445
msgid ""
"deprecate --report option in favour of a new shorter and easier to remember -"
"r option: it takes a string argument consisting of any combination of 'xfsX' "
"characters.  They relate to the single chars you see during the dotted "
"progress printing and will print an extra line per test at the end of the "
"test run.  This extra line indicates the exact position or test ID that you "
"directly paste to the py.test cmdline in order to re-run a particular test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8453
msgid ""
"allow external plugins to register new hooks via the new "
"pytest_addhooks(pluginmanager) hook.  The new release of the pytest-xdist "
"plugin for distributed and looponfailing testing requires this feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8458
msgid ""
"add a new pytest_ignore_collect(path, config) hook to allow projects and "
"plugins to define exclusion behaviour for their directory structure - for "
"example you may define in a conftest.py this method::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8462
msgid ""
"def pytest_ignore_collect(path):\n"
"    return path.check(link=1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8465
msgid "to prevent even a collection try of any tests in symlinked dirs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8467
msgid ""
"new pytest_pycollect_makemodule(path, parent) hook for allowing "
"customization of the Module collection object for a matching test module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8471
msgid ""
"extend and refine xfail mechanism: ``@py.test.mark.xfail(run=False)`` do not "
"run the decorated test ``@py.test.mark.xfail(reason=\"...\")`` prints the "
"reason string in xfail summaries specifying ``--runxfail`` on command line "
"virtually ignores xfail markers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8476
msgid ""
"expose (previously internal) commonly useful methods: py.io."
"get_terminal_with() -> return terminal width py.io.ansi_print(...) -> print "
"colored/bold text on linux/win32 py.io.saferepr(obj) -> return limited "
"representation string"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8481
msgid ""
"expose test outcome related exceptions as py.test.skip.Exception, py.test."
"raises.Exception etc., useful mostly for plugins doing special outcome "
"interpretation/tweaking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8485
